d><p>Issued by the Office of the N.Y. Secretary of State that NJG duly elected Rep. in Congress.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_be879a794bfe8a88444afd4d06974dc6" level="file"><did><unittitle>Other certificates of election</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1916/1920" type="inclusive">1916-1920</unitdate><container id="aspace_0f668aeaf84702500bd432009b8f6373" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_bf2abcb66a4add8c3c7c7a52d0eed1f0" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from C. H. Betts</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1923-03-02/1923-03-07" type="inclusive">1923-03-02-1923-03-07</unitdate><container id="aspace_5a4b3884111c6eece9779d891011fe4b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_784ef975344adf06ab9745711611fb34"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Editor of The Lyons Republican - regrets NJG not running again and commends him.  Also, answer March 7, 1923</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_5c4f2e46fd57926999d9b82f527afc36" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Hattie B. Hardman</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1923-03-16/1923-03-23" type="inclusive">1923-03-16-1923-03-23</unitdate><container id="aspace_46848bab743ecb9fd746adb3454512f5" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_3d79cd9cd2bd69c9270c7c291f3ec312"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Vice-Chairman of Yates County Republican County Committee, expressing regrets at NJG's retirement March 16, 1923; answer March 23rd.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_be286da39467dc1673b122bb049ae7b4" level="file"><did><unittitle>Clipping from Penn Yan newspaper</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_1ecd4b9f3a7c5050d40db79f1dcf9033" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_78ed830e39bd72971a80d4b7b34e28f6" level="file"><did><unittitle>Printed copy of speech</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1918-05-13/1918-05-14" type="inclusive">1918-05-13-1918-05-14</unitdate><container id="aspace_fc25c6b17517f562099b985147ddac9e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_f5d63cc7d14662254b433ffb9b11337e"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Printed copy of speech on Improvement of Functions of the Aircraft Administration.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_8dc0869627d2e095baf100cef3630d69" level="file"><did><unittitle>Old Scrapbook Page</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1870/1879" type="inclusive">1870-1879</unitdate><container id="aspace_80508fced3f02f16ea29514c29406543" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_98c11acf9e72fa969062bb31485b15a3"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page from an old scrapbook dating from the 1870's; includes a notice of the wedding of Seabury S. Gould, Jr. to Minnie Judd of Chicago.  Sr. died 1886</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_cac4ebcbe3f147acd3237303635f3151" level="file"><did><unittitle>Three photos</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1861/1865" type="inclusive">1861-1865</unitdate><container id="aspace_2e17c8cd8b8fc54ae5aa7f1b73f41b4d" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_c1bad08a9ac4c906b90fb80135ce1bbe"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>2 photos of Norman B. Judd (grey beard), 1 photo of same with wife taken in Berlin, where he was U.S. Minister to Germany 1861-1865</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_5bef81fd3501b0f6958d006543ceffef" level="file"><did><unittitle>Seneca Falls Reveille</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1870-07-22/1870-07-22" type="inclusive">1870-07-22</unitdate><container id="aspace_4c5d5856844573b3391cd905cb94693c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_a0bbb28b0ed3d444816c267ede162e1b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>One issue of The Seneca Falls Reveille, Friday, July 22, 1870.  P. 3 has article on Goulds Mfg. Co.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_bc75961df483d7cc660619456cbd9b81" level="file"><did><unittitle>Rochester Democrat and Chronicle</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1938-10-31/1938-10-31" type="inclusive">1938-10-31</unitdate><container id="aspace_7d42b2048981f4d7242a529300756b7b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_ae17856cdf2333e4879946d463e44745"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page from Rochester Democrat and Chronicle, October 31, 1938, "Goulds to Mark 90th Year As Industry in Seneca Falls."</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_2fdddf008083923ba87f2d63edad3f54" level="file"><did><unittitle>Pamphlet</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_1928032e4ea5103c19703a31aa49917c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_c947deba1a1d1309a2f4d7aa22fde7df"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Gould Pumps Incorporated, Seneca Falls, N.Y.  1 pc.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_7f71dc44ff86b497f13fd6ce06e9d51a" level="file"><did><unittitle>Catalogue</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1888/1889" type="inclusive">1888-1889</unitdate><container id="aspace_5bc1582f2248a41a4d56705c7bb9b0ed" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_6c310fd847c438c40645f02647ffa3a1"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The Goulds Manufacturing Co. Pumps and Hydraulic Machinery, Seneca Falls, N.Y., U.S.A., Twenty-Seventh Edition.  1 item.   (removed from Smith collection (# 571?) and added to this collection.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_c13d500a6f7f54c8405153a08f6a894b" level="file"><did><unittitle>Scrapbook</unittitle><container id="aspace_93ece296c1891e762f60e2d745609d80" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_01640c086da0afcc0ef8e8b7bcdd4597" level="item"><did><unittitle>21 bills and 5 resolutions</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1918-12-17/1919-02-08" type="inclusive">1918-12-17-1919-02-08</unitdate><container id="aspace_383ce2fda37a4797cc7e6bd03339c47e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_999e11b1662886f9be05f7b657870295"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 1 - Concerning Prize money for destruction of 1st submarine.   Radio station (commercial) between U.S. and Hawaii, Guam and Philippines.  Provision of tobacco for enlisted men of the Army, Navy and Marine Corps.  National Defense. Provision for Aircraft Administration.  Candy rations for A.E.F., Navy.  Temporary increase of the Military Establishment.  Provision for surgical and medical treatment for men of Armed Services who have been honorably discharged.  Retention of uniform by all hon. discharged men.  Full pay for same.  Relief for commissioned officers, noncoms, and enlisted persons in the Army, Navy, Marine Corps, Coast Guard, and Army Nurse Corps.   Purchase of land for military cemeteries abroad.  Federal aid for States in construction of rural post roads.  Numerous other bills, including establishment of Bureau of War Risk Insurance in the Treasury Dept. Feb 8, 1919</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_80ea3147916cdf423cb78794c2a9ed4d" level="item"><did><unittitle>Resolutions and bills</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1919-02-08/1919-05-19" type="inclusive">1919-02-08-1919-05-19</unitdate><container id="aspace_db172bb1daca2738a90e5f1c8748efaa" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_02cd3ae0e17dd34598a8a4ac6db53772"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 2 - Concerning U.S. Food Administration.  U.S. Shipping Board.   Protection of U.S. interests in Mexico, March 1, 1919</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_7ba2d299ac0c547ab04afa57416250ac" level="item"><did><unittitle>Resolutions</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1919-05-19/1921-05-21" type="inclusive">1919-05-19-1921-05-21</unitdate><container id="aspace_61c64009218a022d35cde5c86f1588d5" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_83fd6bfd1de9d7d66c8c63f23699b644"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 3 - Concerning U.S. Food Administration.  Military Prisons.  Protection of U.S. interests in Mexico, May 19, 1919.  Rural delivery routes.  Prevent District of Columbia police from joining labor organizations.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_1494523fa70542528aebcc97b85fba07" level="item"><did><unittitle>Form letter by the "Norman J. Gould Election Committee for Cayuga County"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1920-10-22/1920-10-22" type="inclusive">1920-10-22</unitdate><container id="aspace_532f2ad52a77eb885805fb9938aa1647" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8d84660d3f63035d71e2fd10ccdaecae"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 4 - 2 pp. giving list of various bills and resolutions in the interest of soldiers and sailors intro. By NJG.  Also, typescript data on each of above bills and resolutions, giving explanation of background for each, action taken by appropriate dept. 28 pcs.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_7970dceceddd7476e792649dba66d069" level="item"><did><unittitle>Mounted Pamphlet</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1919-03-03/1919-03-03" type="inclusive">1919-03-03</unitdate><container id="aspace_ae6b543a035eeb418f922b1fa5ac03f1" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_9baf1d24e29166ad8072d6fcca04481b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 5 - Copy of speech re: "Foreign trade section of the Bond Bill with respect to the situation in Mexico."  20 pp.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_025fb3d3663704881e71f16f84c6a0c7" level="item"><did><unittitle>Mounted Pamphlet</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917-04-05/1917-04-05" type="inclusive">1917-04-05</unitdate><container id="aspace_34a5f536588d42542fe9450c85f6a761" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_ac144ef4280e681d3f8c39f2807bb37a"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Copy of speech re: War with Germany."   8 pp.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_ac71a24a32117f7609de157c7cd3f323" level="item"><did><unittitle>Mounted Pamphlet</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1918-05-13/1918-05-14" type="inclusive">1918-05-13-1918-05-14</unitdate><container id="aspace_9bf1174b7775c406a063de28a6c1789d" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_2ebedc54295133d4cdfb1ae8e93ecb1f"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Copy of speech re: "To Improve the Functions of the Aircraft Administration,"   8 pp.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_9336218efe7a874b3d300e8d4351e30b" level="item"><did><unittitle>Press release</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922-06-10/1922-06-10" type="inclusive">1922-06-10</unitdate><container id="aspace_6eb7576a6505a6b793e4d3991e9fc413" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_0deae2e61db47f7daec9718bc64a01d4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Announcing that NJG will run for Congress again.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_b769f01d827ddc895da0910507a6d25e" level="item"><did><unittitle>Press release</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1918-04-12/1918-04-12" type="inclusive">1918-04-12</unitdate><container id="aspace_ba7403b69aeaee15edbb4f323b0ae920" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_3e88d2336e3c236b234f5ef1be807bbc"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Aircraft Production Bd.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_e96a1cbf0f7a9b26601ca5281912d46c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Form letter to Constituents</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1921-09-29/1921-09-29" type="inclusive">1921-09-29</unitdate><container id="aspace_1ac9be68db3461e839cc676718650ec4" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8d4a2aedca5f5adb9af2a79701a41790"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Form letter concerning rural mail delivery and efforts made by Gould on behalf of citizens of Cayuga and Wayne Counties.  2 pp.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_2658db3ff4c8424cf9f5e9b7160e1eb7" level="item"><did><unittitle>Page from Congressional letter</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922-03-23/1922-03-23" type="inclusive">1922-03-23</unitdate><container id="aspace_f5a755e208fc3528f774596b247693eb" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_d2d2d8886261abe794f562b4d63a45b3"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Containing speech in which NJG states that he will vote against the Soldiers' Bonus Bill and telling why.  1 pc.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_e410fd15cc08d0f88e261df67bde0a79" level="item"><did><unittitle>4th of July Patriotic Speech</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917-07-04/1917-07-04" type="inclusive">1917-07-04</unitdate><container id="aspace_2da40ef62a32d2fc429891c64b665ec5" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_f1c058f5bed918430c9deece51364e9b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Speech made by NJG in Seneca Falls, re: U.S. War effort, the draft, need for sacrifice, more $$ for airplanes, food control.  (8 pp. typescript carbon)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_65b462235086556318c88bfbe084accc" level="item"><did><unittitle>Gould's statement</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1921-10-08/1921-10-08" type="inclusive">1921-10-08</unitdate><container id="aspace_cf4fbaa9543c319ad785642ba20e0d14" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_0a8ae2f3713b50e06ab446d6bc40708f"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>re: resolution for investigation of the use of federal funds for agricultural org.  (1 pc. Mimeograph)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_c37b9b6d2b8f3ff80b2f6d168b2c272e" level="item"><did><unittitle>Printed statement</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1920-08-09/1920-08-09" type="inclusive">1920-08-09</unitdate><container id="aspace_1457b982a92b6ce69d45f763584af838" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_6edb25af27ced98a4ab94cf3c76d7e6b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Announcing NJG's candidacy for renomination on the Republican ticket for member of Congress   (1 pc.)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_8470aa70f416ec09b14158ecf1f50fc9" level="item"><did><unittitle>Statement of NJG</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917-02-14/1917-02-14" type="inclusive">1917-02-14</unitdate><container id="aspace_fe95f3ecbbd9323c08fbe61ae29e6b09" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_b27248a9cbb8b86f5534413e7dabbee7"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>re: estimates filed by Labor Dept. for the U.S. Employment Service for next fiscal year, apparently before an investigating committee.  (Failures in functioning of USES: irregular activities of staff: opposition to a peacetime USES.  (12 pcs.)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_0adf27cf3a28b48636fe3ed5fca28adc" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letters to Gould</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922-04/1922-06-15" type="inclusive">1922-04-1922-06-15</unitdate><container id="aspace_bea67a04a6e05982944aaf08e86bf443" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_0ea4a3f4bea6eb4f085bf77a4c057df5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 6 -  Letters from constituents and others commending NJG for voting against the bonus bill; includes one from the Rev. Charles K. Imbrie, chaplain of the Penn Yan American Legion Post; also from school superintendents, manufacturers, lawyers, etc.  Other letters urging Gould to run for Congress again and expressing regrets that he has decided not to do so; including one from Charles E. Treman, June 15, 1922.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_71360251b31239ea817211d0371c98a4" level="item"><did><unittitle>letters</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922/1922" type="inclusive">1922</unitdate><container id="aspace_cf634dc311ae811e444221ae9bb56f98" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_3356aec6f6b881f443e63b45a83fa12d"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 7 - More letters concerning bonus.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_9213b9f1bb89870784813859cb46648c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Newspaper clippings</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1922/1922" type="inclusive">1922</unitdate><container id="aspace_dd226e4ddffc1810beb1bef656d9752b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_98dce6e26e943168a7825ef623ed2ef8"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 8 - Newspaper clippings re: Gould's retirement from Congress in 1922 and John Taber's candidacy.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_68823a54ba8954ecd01f43afdd3b66d8" level="item"><did><unittitle>Clippings</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_da931e66b298993d1899091a1d977f84" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_5483a8671021fddda5d93769d4ae1e01"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 9 - Clippings re: position NJG took on various questions while serving in Congress.  Also, letter from NJG giving his estimate of James W. Wadsworth.  Some clippings re: Snell, other NYS Congressmen.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_1fbd9ea13b98f19c0ecbc24d5d38f19c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Clippings</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_562d567b1136eb29b1d9bccc8d8b2eaa" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_e2ecb5a38285bcd75a9416efbd649cc4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 10 - Clippings re: introduction of bill for reorg. of aircraft division.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_e990136c7d1f8ab0097ac48a0d7c3d0f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Snapshots and printed material</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1917/1917" type="inclusive">1917</unitdate><container id="aspace_9e153c3746ae923c69030b1b7e8bbac0" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_02ae3652097f25c5124461743369b205"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 11 - Two photos of a Labor Day Parade, 1917  (Seneca Falls?).  Christmas card with photo of the Black Watch pipers on parade.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_8364067faf92e9361ee6baa80a212c25" level="item"><did><unittitle>Original pen and ink sketch</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1920-03-31/1920-03-31" type="inclusive">1920-03-31</unitdate><container id="aspace_39b60e1ddd5aef20c16c63a885bd54a0" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_7bda4d8863d6c01ffe5e8ba44c4a4f70"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Sketch of cartoon of Gould at wheel of a speeding car.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_5beee9243f7d4f0250b510a833b1a836" level="item"><did><unittitle>Cartoon</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_16882536c8e58957f7544b3f391a0671" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8d8595ae3992fe7c4db8645dd12888bd"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Cartoon from The Evening Bulletin (Philadelphia), re: Congressmen who voted in favor of Prohibition.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_957c84223ac7fe47f5a6b657998d8dbc" level="item"><did><unittitle>Mimeo. Announcement</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_70a9d8bbc64ec693939b6f816a1e62fe" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_71bff2a157e41e467663ce673f72b4ac"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>re: bills sponsored by Gould.  4 pcs.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_2bd6e973441647ef827eea9a276c4b41" level="item"><did><unittitle>Typescript unsigned letter</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1918-09-18/1919-01-27" type="inclusive">1918-09-18-1919-01-27</unitdate><container id="aspace_d3e3dbe22ed9c176f62aee58d743944c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_550d985c25461bd29ad2e4c50bf76ce9"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Typescript of unsigned letter (copy?) with clipping pasted on from a Sgt. in France, Sept 18, 1918, commending Gould for resolution that candy be added to ratio., Typescript carbon of second letter, Jan. 27, 1919, from same re: same and expressing opinions on conditions in Germany and attitude of conquered Germans.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_7de9ab3d786699f21c47178a0f8ec6bc" level="item"><did><unittitle>Photostat</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_d97dbed175670524ce0d91b560d08028" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_1545713564c81c485e8d867b737c088f"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Photostat of printed statement from National Security League of NYC re: votes of Congressmen on 8 war measures.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_731091c44db82db6e14e363908e23454" level="item"><did><unittitle>Congressional Directory</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_bef54f5695fb2db6d137ce98f5aa0e2a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_ae758651140712002fc5815a5799e831"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 12 - Pages torn from Congressional Directory, containing information on NJG.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_2f9d9c1d8e8a4869ce689d8054feae81" level="item"><did><unittitle>Issue of The Morning Star</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1920-03-31/1920-03-31" type="inclusive">1920-03-31</unitdate><container id="aspace_669af6f8f95c23fc276e03ad1322081c" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_ef28c2bbf5da93dc77382034d5d256e5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Issue of The Morning Star (Washington, D.C.) March 31, 1920 - trick photos, Humorous comment, cartoons on current political situation.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_bb139570040d951a684eddf2e2df0fa9" level="item"><did><unittitle>One clipping</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1930-11-09/1930-11-09" type="inclusive">1930-11-09</unitdate><container id="aspace_0f2ce6dbb249b740bd0c29cc29c6f723" label="Mixed Materials [31924065235917]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_8c7fb64505e8a3ef5f451b3cbae1c2b8"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Page 13 - Letter from Martha Freeman Esmond to friend, Julia Boyd of New York, re: wedding of Norman B. Judd's daughter, Miss Minnie Judd to Seabury S. Gould (Junior) (father of Norman J. Gould).  Chicago, March 31, 1875.  Printed in Chicago Sunday Tribune, November 9, 1930.</p></scopecontent></c02></c01></dsc>
